        "content": "<p>Do we have the fact that semiconjugate matrices share an eigenvalue?</p>",
        "id": 283808094,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1653427967
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Do we even have eigenvalues of matrices?</p>",
        "id": 283809017,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1653428574
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Oh this is really a statement about endomorphisms actually. Note that not all of them have to be of the same type. We can have <code>f : \\a -&gt; \\a</code>, <code>g : \\a -&gt; \\b</code>, <code>h : \\b -&gt; \\b</code> and the hypothesis <code>f • g = g • h</code>.</p>",
        "id": 283810656,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1653429600
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Did you mean ∘?</p>",
        "id": 283812786,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1653430712
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>f • g</code> doesn't typecheck there</p>",
        "id": 283812865,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1653430759
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yes sorry I'm on my phone</p>",
        "id": 283814236,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1653431567
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Do we have that the transpose of a matrix <code>A</code> has the same eigenvalues as <code>A</code>? or rather the endomorphism version?</p>",
        "id": 283866411,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1653475971
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Presumably the endomorphism version is a statement about duals. Does it need a finite-dimensionality hypothesis?</p>",
        "id": 283872861,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1653480256
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think not</p>",
        "id": 283872941,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1653480322
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Or would it be a statement about <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs/find/linear_map.adjoint\">docs#linear_map.adjoint</a> / <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs/find/continuous_linear_map.adjoint\">docs#continuous_linear_map.adjoint</a>?</p>",
        "id": 283876337,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1653482443
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I would finger guess <code>linear_map.adjoint</code> indeed.</p>",
        "id": 283883154,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1653485730
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That one _does_ require finite-dimensionality</p>",
        "id": 283885591,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1653486861
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You don't need inner products for the endomorphism version, you can formulate it in terms of <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs/find/module.dual.transpose\">docs#module.dual.transpose</a>. I'm pretty sure that we don't have the statement for endomorphisms, given that we didn't even have the fact that the trace is the same until three days ago.</p>",
        "id": 283904680,
        "sender_full_name": "Antoine Labelle",
        "timestamp": 1653495006
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But I don’t think it will work in infinite dimensional spaces</p>",
        "id": 283929408,
        "sender_full_name": "Anatole Dedecker",
        "timestamp": 1653506594
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In general you can only prove that an eigenvalue of <code>f</code> is an eigenvalue of its transpose, but <em>I think</em> I have a counterexample for the converse</p>",
        "id": 283929656,
        "sender_full_name": "Anatole Dedecker",
        "timestamp": 1653506718
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think that the k-linear endomorphism of nat -&gt;_0 k sending e_n to e_{n+1} doesn't have any eigenvalues but its dual has loads. What do you think <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"387244\">@Yaël Dillies</span> ?</p>",
        "id": 283934300,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1653509325
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yes, that’s what I had in mind</p>",
